00d33808-84a3-4631-9740-6cc6fbcb7753	00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000000d1	Quam Securities — Dealing Reference & House Rules	quam-dealing-reference.md	QUAM SECURITIES — DEALING REFERENCE & HOUSE RULES\nInternal trade-desk reference for call-quality and compliance review.\n\n1. HONG KONG STOCK CODES (HKEX Main Board)\nOfficial Hong Kong Stock Exchange codes for frequently traded counters:\n- 騰訊控股 Tencent Holdings — stock code 700\n- 友邦保險 AIA Group — stock code 1299\n- 中國平安 Ping An Insurance — stock code 2318\n- 中國銀行 Bank of China — stock code 3988\n- 建設銀行 China Construction Bank — stock code 939\n- 匯豐控股 HSBC Holdings — stock code 5\n- 美團 Meituan — stock code 3690\n- 小米集團 Xiaomi — stock code 1810\n- 阿里巴巴 Alibaba Group — stock code 9988\n- 中國移動 China Mobile — stock code 941\n- 比亞迪股份 BYD — stock code 1211\n- 工商銀行 ICBC — stock code 1398\n- 香港交易所 HKEX — stock code 388\n\n2. TRADING HOURS (HKEX securities market, Hong Kong time)\n- Pre-opening session: 09:00 to 09:30\n- Morning continuous trading: 09:30 to 12:00\n- Afternoon continuous trading: 13:00 to 16:00\nThe market is closed on Saturdays, Sundays and HKEX public holidays.\n\n3. SETTLEMENT\nSecurities trades settle on a T+2 basis — two business days after the trade date.\n\n4. BROKERAGE COMMISSION AND FEES\n- Standard brokerage commission: 0.25% of trade value, minimum HKD 100 per trade.\n- Statutory charges per side: stamp duty 0.1%, SFC transaction levy 0.0027%, HKEX trading fee 0.00565%.\n\n5. ORDER TYPES AND EXECUTION\n- Market order (市價盤): fills at the best available price in the market.\n- Limit order (限價盤): fills only at the specified price or better.\n- A large order may be filled in one or more tranches (partial fills, 分批成交) as matching liquidity becomes available; brokers may fill an order in several batches in the market.\n- At-auction limit orders may be entered during the pre-opening session.\n\n6. CLIENT PLATFORM AND NOTIFICATIONS\n- Clients can view real-time quotes, account balances and positions, and place orders on the Quam mobile app and online trading platform.\n- When an order is executed, the client receives an SMS or push notification confirming the fill.\n\n7. DEALING CONDUCT (mandatory)\n- Verify the client's identity (full name and account number) before accepting any instruction.\n- Read back the complete order (stock name or code, buy or sell, quantity and price) and obtain the client's explicit confirmation before placing it.\n- Give the standard risk disclosure ("the price of securities may go down as well as up") before accepting an order from a non-professional client.\n- Inform the client that the call is recorded for quality and compliance purposes.\n	ready	4	\N	2026-06-17 02:30:32.763348+00
\.
